Author:  WARD
Vol / Page:  180
Edition:
Quote:  Information had been laid against a resident of Karori, for a breach of the Municipal Bye-Law, by tying his horse up to as to interrupt traffic on the footpath. An apology induced the Magistrate to dismiss the defendant wth a caution, and a reminder that the streets of Wellington were not now so unfrequented that the ancient practice could be continued with impunity.
Notes:  Dates from 1876
